---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  description="Aadi Labs is building self-improving, pluralistically aligned intelligence: the last intelligence software you'll ever need, useful from day one without a learning curve."
>
  <main class="container" role="main">
    <section class="content">
      <p>
        We're building AI that self-improves and collaborates with
        people and teams to reach what neither could alone: built to
        10x agency and ambition, not replace them.
      </p>

      <h2>Models are not products.</h2>

      <p>
        Today's AI doesn't learn from you. The model is frozen at ship;
        the harness is static; memory features store facts but the
        system doesn't get sharper because you used it yesterday. A
        truly intelligent product does the opposite: invisible
        underneath, evolves to fit the person using it, gets sharper on
        its own.
      </p>

      <h2>Two research bets.</h2>

      <ul class="bet-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Continual learning</strong>: systems that keep getting
          sharper from real production use, without regressing on what
          they already got right.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pluralistic alignment</strong>: staying true to the
          specific person or organization, not a population average.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>We own the stack.</h2>

      <p>
        We're not a wrapper around someone else's API. The whole stack,
        from research to product, is ours. That lets us take bets other
        labs won't, change direction with evidence, and put every
        interaction to work twice: serving the user now, training what
        comes next. Not one model for millions, but millions of
        distinct intelligences, each diverging into something only its
        user has.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this matters.</h2>

      <p>
        Intelligence at this scale only works as co-evolution. The
        system gets sharper the longer you use it. You get more capable
        the longer you have it. The relationship is the unit of
        progress.
      </p>

      <p>
        A lot of capability and creativity is local &mdash; one person,
        one community, one tradition of craft. Most never compounds
        into anything visible because the leverage isn't there.
        Ramanujan almost didn't reach the world. The next decade of AI
        is the difference between finding the next one and never
        knowing they existed.
      </p>

      <h2>Who's building it.</h2>

      <p>
        Mission-driven small team at the intersection of AI research
        and design. Battle-tested in building products for billions of
        users and top tech companies.
      </p>

      <h2>Two products. One engine.</h2>

      <div class="products">
        <article class="product">
          <p class="product-eyebrow">Waitlist open</p>
          <h3 class="product-name">
            <a
              class="product-link"
              href="https://jinnie.ai"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener">Jinnie</a
            >
          </h3>
          <p class="product-meta">For one person, or a small team.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="product">
          <p class="product-eyebrow">Organizations &middot; in development</p>
          <h3 class="product-name">Sal</h3>
          <p class="product-meta">In development.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
      <script is:inline>
        /* Reveal the products section once it enters the viewport.
           Progressive enhancement: initial CSS leaves content visible
           so no-JS readers and reduced-motion users see it immediately.
           This script *opts in* to the hidden start state, then animates. */
        (function () {
          var el = document.currentScript.previousElementSibling;
          if (!el) return;
          if (window.matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches) return;
          el.classList.add("reveal-ready");
          var io = new IntersectionObserver(
            function (entries) {
              entries.forEach(function (entry) {
                if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                  entry.target.classList.add("is-revealed");
                  io.unobserve(entry.target);
                }
              });
            },
            { threshold: 0.15, rootMargin: "0px 0px -10% 0px" }
          );
          io.observe(el);
        })();
      </script>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
